import React from 'react' import { useSelector } from 'react-redux' const Details = () => { const detailsState = useSelector ((state) => state.details) console.log(detailsState) return (

{detailsState.id}

{detailsState.title}

{detailsState.summary}

{detailsState.healthScore}

{detailsState.analyzedInstructions}

{detailsState.Diets?.map(t =>

{t.name}

)}
{console.log()}
) } export default Details
